Business Mogul and Philanthropist, Chief Ambassador Yohana Margif has been endorsed by the Labour Party (LP) as the sole governorship candidate of the party in the Plateau State gubernatorial election. The development came barely three days after Margif withdrew from the All Progressive Congress (APC) in Plateau to climb to the LP ticket. Margif, who accepted the nomination form of the Labor Party at a brief reception hosted by the National Chairman of the party, Barr. Julius Abure in Abuja at the weekend called on the party to believe in him as their new symbol of unity and development in the state. -Advertisement- According to him, a lot is still needed to be done in order to restore the lost Glory of Plateau, adding that many citizens are still outside hungry, unemployed and many more threatened by unwarranted and unnecessary security and economic challenges. Earlier in his remarks, the National Chairman of the party, who was flanked by Comrade Adi Shirsha Adi, the National Vice Chairman North Central Zone, the Plateau State chairperson of the Party, Grace Zamfara and other stakeholders of the Party expressed confidence in Chief Ambassador Yohana Margif, describing him as a leader who understands the Problems of Plateau and assured him of the Partyâ€™s support towards the realization of the aspiration. According to the National Chairman of the Party, Plateau is in dear need of true and genuine leaders like Margif who will tackle insecurity for famers to access their farms, and revamp the state economy to create employment for youths in the state.